node.title: Third Omicron COVID-19 case 'possibly' found in NSW: Premier
node.description: The NSW Premier says a third overseas traveller has "possibly" tested positive to the new Omicron COVID-19 variant.
node.content: ["NSW Premier Dominic Perrottet says a third overseas traveller has \"possibly\" tested positive to the new Omicron COVID-19 variant.", "Yesterday\u00a0NSW Health confirmed two returned travellers have tested positive for the new variant in Sydney, making them the first known cases of the strain in Australia.", "This morning, he revealed another person had \"possibly\" tested positive for Omicron.", "Mr Perrottet said\u00a0141 people from\u00a0nine southern African countries impacted by the variant \u2014 South Africa, Lesotho, Botswana, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Namibia, Eswatini, Malawi\u00a0\u2014 had arrived in NSW over the past 24 hours and were in quarantine.", "New rules introduced on Saturday in response to the Omicron variant mean anyone arriving in NSW from these countries must isolate in a health facility\u00a0for 14 days.", "Scientists around the world are working to discover if the Omicron variant is more infectious than other strains of COVID, and whether it is more resistant to vaccines.", "Mr Perrottet said his government was \"working very closely\" with the Commonwealth, and that national cabinet would convene later today, or tomorrow, to discuss the new variant.", "\"We don't just need to live alongside COVID, we need to learn to live alongside the variants as well,\" he said.", "\"Ultimately we need to open up to the world [and] we need to do so safely, we don\u2019t need to have a knee-jerk reaction, we need to have a proportionate and balanced response.\"", "The Premier said the government did not plan to\u00a0reintroduce hotel quarantine for international arrivals and that\u00a0he was \"confident\" the high vaccination rate in NSW would keep the community safe.", "He said it was \"too early\" to say what the next steps in combating the variant would be.", "The tightened travel rules in response to Omicron mean passengers arriving in NSW from anywhere in the world must now isolate at their place of residence or accommodation for 72 hours\u00a0further health advice.", "More to come."]
